#+TITLE: Alerting / Announcing

* Alerting & Announcing

The basics and some less obvious alerts:

** 1C: *ALERT*

- 1!c--1!d/1N or higher: *alert* (totally artificial or unexpected strengths)

** 1D: "may be zero, maybe 4--5 minors when natural"

- 1!d--1!h/1!s: *alert* (maybe light hate !ds, major minor canap√©)
- 1!d--2!h/2!s: *alert* (two way reverse flannery, NF)
- 1!d--3!c/3!d/3!h/3!s/4!c/4!d: *alert* (NF new suit)

** 1H/1S: ""

- 1M--1N: "up to bad 12 points"
- 1!h--2!s: *alert* (NF new suit)
- 1!h/1!s--3new: *alert* (NF invitational new suit)
- 1M--2new: "Game Forcing"
- 1M--3M: *alert* (mixed raise)
- 1!h--3!s: *alert* (some weaker splinter)
- 1!h--3N: *alert* (!s splinter)
- 1!s--3N: *alert* (some weaker splinter)
- 1!s--4x: *alert* (splinter)

** 1N: "16 to 18"

- 1N--2!c: "Stayman"
- 1N--2!c--2!d: not alerted
- 1N--2!d: "Hearts" (2 level red suit transfers)
- 1N--2!h: "Spades"
- 1N--2!s: *alert* (range ask or "Clubs")
- 1N--2N: "Diamonds"

** 2C: "Intermediate"

- 2!c--2!h/2!s: *alert* (NF new suit)
- 2!c--2N+: *alert* (all artificial, transfers etc.)
- 2!c--4!c: *alert* (mixed, not invitational)

** 2D: *ALERT*

- 2!d--2N: *alert* (forcing)
- 2!d--3!d/4!d: *alert* (preemptive, not invitational)

** 2H: "Weak"

** 2S: "Weak"

** 2N: ""

- 2N--3!c: *alert* (5 card muppet)
- 2N--3!c--3!d: *alert* (may have 4 cards)
- 2N--3!d: "Hearts"
- 2N--3!h: "Spades"

** Any Sequence 3N+: alerted only before opener's 2nd bid
